  "@type": "Domain",
  "critical": false,
  "description": "Industrial-scale transformation of raw agricultural output into stable, safe, transportable food products. Spans grain milling (stone to roller), food preservation (drying through refrigeration), dairy processing (separation, butter, cheese), and brewing/distilling (beer, wine, spirits). Food processing feeds the workforce that builds GPUs — without it, no specialist labor pool exists. Internal organizing axis: chronological, from stone-age techniques to industrial processes.",
  "early_win": true,
  "early_win_note": "Flour from milling and preserved food from drying/salting create food surplus stability, enabling specialist labor division",
